Following a two-day national executive committee meeting Njabulo Nzuza the league s secretary general said on Tuesday the ANCYL wanted leadership that would implement radical economic transformation.That meant people who would pursue the following;The ANCYL put the following names forward:Nzuza said the league was of the view that there was a need to have two deputy secretaries general to deal with issues of monitoring evaluation and campaigns.He said the youth league would release its own critique of the ANC discussion documents asserting youth interest as part of its contribution to the national policy conference.The league also wants the ANC to look beyond credentials of going to exile when electing leadership and consider leaders with a good track record produced post 1994.